{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Make it illegal to discriminate against someone based on their expressed opinion",
        "additional_details": "If the petition\u2019s proposals became law then people would be protected from discrimination based on their expressed opinions.\r\n \r\nThis would mean that employers and businesses could not choose to discriminate, or be pressured into discriminating, against people on the basis of their expressed opinions.\r\n \r\nIt should also allow greater freedom to debate important issues.",
        "background": "Bodies or individuals committing such discrimination should be liable for criminal prosecution. The wronged person should have legal rights to compensation for mental suffering and financial loss.\r\n\r\nThe only exemption would be if the person had been convicted for illegally expressing their opinion.",
